<br>
 Many things they advertise for EQ still are missing, I can go through the list but if you have been playing Im sure you can name quite a few. The last 3 expansions or 2 if you dont count LoY as a true expansion, have been shipped incomplete to meet a deadline that shouldnt have been set for whatever reasons. Im not sure of the exact reason why they were not finished but some stuff is still not finished.<br>
<br>
 EQ2 has not gone through any form of beta but yet they are confident with a christmas release date. Im not positive but all I remember seeing is a few screen shots without any video of the game being played or anything other than screens for E3. SOE isnt shy about bragging and showing off their product, if they have the goods. So the question is why have we not seen much? If I was to bet it would be because many things are no where near finished. They are trying to rush it out the door for whatever reason, maybe to beat WoW, make more money, who knows.<br>
<br>
 If the game is 50 percent finished no matter how good it looks, it will be horrid to play. Im not sure if many SOE devs read the board much any more but if you happen to see this, please take the time necessary to finish the game. Releasing something half finished just to get it out there or beat one of SOE managements deadline will hurt the game before it gets a chance to start.<br>
<br>
 For me I will have to wait and see how it goes, after the past few years with EQ and SOE, I am very reluctant to ever pay for another one of their products. This is just a few reasons SOE has a lot of work to do and prove they are serious about making the best product they can, not making it the fastest and being the first to get it on the shelf.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=filanfyretracker>Filan Fyretracker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1918<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/03 1:08:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26483.topic&index=60>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/filanwizard/wtcsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 Website up</span><hr size=1> Planetside has been doing well, though i dont have the retail version it got pretty good at the end of beta and i was on till they booted us all on sunday night. <p><html><center><a href="mailto:filan@snet.net"><img 

